<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy — Cricket Book</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --gold: #C5A028;
      --gold-dark: #8B7321;
      --ink: #1A1A1A;
      --muted: #4A4A4A;
      --paper: #F9F9F7;
      --card: #FFFFFF;
      --line: #E4E4DE;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(180deg, #FDFDFB 0%, #EBEBE6 100%);
      color: var(--ink);
      line-height: 1.65;
      padding: 24px 16px 64px;
    }
    .wrap { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
    header {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 32px 20px 24px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--gold);
      margin-bottom: 28px;
    }
    .crest {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      width: 56px; height: 56px;
      border: 2px solid var(--gold);
      border-radius: 14px;
      font-size: 26px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      background: var(--paper);
    }
    h1 {
      font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: 30px;
      letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    }
    .updated { color: var(--muted); font-size: 14px; margin-top: 6px; }
    .card {
      background: var(--card);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 16px;
      padding: 22px 24px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
      box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
    }
    h2 {
      font-family: Georgia, "Times New Roman", serif;
      font-size: 20px;
      color: var(--gold-dark);
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      padding-bottom: 6px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
    }
    p { color: var(--muted); margin-bottom: 12px; }
    p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
    ul { margin: 8px 0 12px 20px; color: var(--muted); }
    li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
    strong { color: var(--ink); }
    a { color: var(--gold-dark); }
    .highlight {
      background: #FBF6E4;
      border-left: 4px solid var(--gold);
      padding: 14px 16px;
      border-radius: 8px;
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 13px;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <header>
      <div class="crest">📖</div>
      <h1>Cricket Book — Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="updated">Last updated: 6 July 2026</div>
    </header>

    <div class="card">
      <p class="highlight">
        Cricket Book is a simple, offline cricket game. We do <strong>not</strong> collect,
        store, sell, or share any personal information. There are no user accounts, no logins,
        and no servers that receive your data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy applies to the <strong>Cricket Book</strong> mobile application
        ("the App", "we", "us", or "our") published by <strong>Aashish Sharma from WhiteCoders</strong>
        (package name: <em>com.whitecoders.cricketbookgame</em>). By downloading or using the
        App, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We do not collect any personal or sensitive user data.</strong> The App does not
        require you to create an account or provide any contact information.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Player names:</strong> Any names you type for players are used only to display
          scores during a match. They are kept temporarily in the device's memory and are discarded
          when the game ends or the App is closed. They are never uploaded anywhere.</li>
        <li><strong>No personal identifiers:</strong> We do not collect your name, email, phone
          number, location, contacts, photos, or device identifiers.</li>
        <li><strong>No analytics or tracking:</strong> The App contains no third-party analytics,
          advertising SDKs, or tracking technologies.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>3. Device Permissions</h2>
      <p>The App uses only minimal, non-sensitive device features:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Vibration / Haptics:</strong> Used to provide tactile feedback for game events
          (runs, boundaries, wickets).</li>
        <li><strong>Audio playback:</strong> Plays short built-in sound effects included with the App.
          No microphone access is used or requested.</li>
        <li><strong>Share:</strong> When you tap "Share Match Card", the App uses your device's
          standard share sheet so you can send an image of your result to apps you choose. We do not
          have access to what you share or whom you share it with.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The App does <strong>not</strong> request access to the camera, microphone, location,
        contacts, storage, or any other sensitive permission.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>4. Data Storage</h2>
      <p>
        The App works fully offline. Game data such as scores and settings exists only on your
        device during play and is not transmitted to us or any third party. Uninstalling the App
        removes all such data.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The App does not integrate advertising networks, analytics providers, or other third-party
        data-collection services. If you choose to share a result, the third-party app you select
        (e.g. a messaging or social app) will handle that content under its own privacy policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Cricket Book is suitable for general audiences. Because the App does not collect any
        personal information from anyone, it does not knowingly collect data from children under 13
        (or the equivalent minimum age in your country). If you believe a child has provided us
        personal data, please contact us and we will address it — though, as noted, no such data is
        collected.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>7. Security</h2>
      <p>
        Since the App does not transmit or store personal data on external servers, the risk of a
        data breach involving your personal information is minimal. All gameplay data remains local
        to your device.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page
        with a revised "Last updated" date. Continued use of the App after changes take effect
        constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the App's privacy practices, please
        contact us at:
      </p>
      <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@whitecoders.example">info@whitecoders.com</a></p>
      <p style="font-size:13px;">(Replace the address above with your official support email before publishing.)</p>
    </div>

    <footer>
      &copy; 2026 White Coders · Cricket Book. All rights reserved.
    </footer>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
